O. DROPPING OF PINAL CONSONANTS.

An accurate student of Plautian prosody will soon observe that, for scanning Plautian verses, he must very often free himself from the observance of the rnles commonly taught under the head of positio. should be at a loss to explain many cases of naturally short vowels lengthened by position. Most¹ of the cases referred to will he explained by the following remarks.
